  "text": "The esterification of oxidized glutathione (GSSG) with thionyl chloride was previously reported [CITATION_1] , but studies monitoring the reaction conversion have not been reported. The disposition toward thionyl chloride acylation is likely due to the incompatibilities often associated with the harsh conditions of thionyl chloride which are subject to both side reactions and incomplete formation of product. Therefore, we set out to study the limitations of this method by monitoring the reaction using ESI-MS in the presence of various alcohols using 1 as a substrate.",
